    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:82038b69-031e-446f-9ded-545c8237770a",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-description</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 73-year-old Czech male, slightly gaunt in appearance with noticeable weight loss over recent months. He presents with a persistent, forceful cough productive of thick, bubbling secretions, accompanied by progressive shortness of breath and significant fatigue [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:0]. He reports a heavy feeling in his chest and occasional chest pain. Over the last several days, his family has noted episodes of confusion and difficulty forming coherent sentences, raising concern for possible brain involvement or electrolyte disturbance [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:7].\n\n{patientName} spent most of his working life as a construction engineer in Brno, Czech Republic, where he had occupational exposure to asbestos dust and various inhalation agents over decades [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:3]. He is a long-standing smoker, having smoked 30 cigarettes per day since his early twenties — a cumulative habit of over 50 pack-years. He retired at 65 and has since enjoyed woodworking and walking in the Moravian countryside, though both activities have become increasingly limited by his breathlessness.\n\n{patientName} lives with his wife of 48 years in a flat in Brno. His two adult children visit regularly and have become more involved in his care as his condition has progressed. He maintains a modest social life, occasionally meeting old colleagues at a local café, though his energy has declined markedly. He reports disturbed sleep, reduced appetite, and has lost approximately 8 kg over the past four months."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:cc206b0d-35fc-4827-bbb6-d7a11a78d8e7",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-history</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has a significant smoking history of over 50 pack-years, representing the primary risk factor for his lung malignancy [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:3]. He also has a history of prolonged occupational exposure to inhalation agents during his construction career [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:3]. He was previously diagnosed with COPD confirmed by pulmonary function testing [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:6], for which he uses an inhaled bronchodilator. He was treated empirically for bronchitis on two occasions in the preceding year before his lung cancer diagnosis was established [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:3]. {patientName} underwent bronchoscopy and CT-guided lung biopsy approximately 8 months ago, which confirmed the malignancy. He subsequently received a course of carboplatin-based chemotherapy. He has hypertension managed with oral medication and mild chronic kidney disease (stage 2). He has no known history of prior hospitalizations for cardiac events. He lives with his wife and reports moderate functional status (ECOG PS 2). Recent neurological deterioration has prompted urgent evaluation for brain metastases and electrolyte imbalance [MEDDIALOG:C34.9:7]."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
